title: Jam From the Dam 2014 Recap
description:
The morning of the second stop of the O'Neill SUP and Paddleboard Series was primed with amazing conditions! The sun was out, the temperature was a perfect 80 degrees and the lake was like a sheet of glass. Once the competitors were lined up, the horn sounded and the start of the race was underway.

Rob Rojas finished 1st in the Unlimited Elite division with a time of 53 minutes and 43 seconds. The next wave of paddlers to come in was Rukin Jelks in the OC1 class, finishing with a total time of 54 minutes and 10 seconds. Following Jelks, Damien Estrada in the Unlimited Open class finished with a time of 54 minutes and 30 seconds. Patrick McNenny took 1st place in the Paddleboard division and Brennan Rose took 1st place in the 14' class.
